There are two distinct projects related to Grain and the Model Context Protocol:

The Grain MCP server is a community-built tool that integrates with the Grain meeting recording service, allowing users to access functions like retrieving meetings and downloading transcripts without needing an enterprise API [1]. It is configured in an MCP client using the following command structure:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "grain_uvx": {
      "command": "uvx",
      "args": [
        "--from", "git+https://github.com/eadm/grain-mcp-server",
        "grain-mcp-server",
        "--user-data-dir", "<absolute-path-to-browser-session-data>"
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

Separately, the Grain project provides its own MCP adapter (`@grain.sh/mcp`) and server (`@grain.sh/mcp-server`), which serve as part of a platform-agnostic, language-based interaction layer for AI agents [2].
